The Telegraph - Calcutta
 A first by an Indian boy 
New Delhi, July 19 (PTI): Viraat Badhwar, a class III student here, has created history by finishing second in the under-8 category in the junior world golf championships held in San Diego. The seven-year-old is the first Indian to finish on the podium in the history of the meet. Badhwar made the cut from a field of 100 and then competed with the top 20 to finish with a card of one over 162 in three days of the championships which concluded Friday.  Copyright 
